    • Method Detail

      • getUuid

        String getUuid()
        Get the unique universal identifier of this asset within the Smint.io platform.

        The UUID will not change, once created for an asset. It is the value to identify the asset with the Smint.io platform and with any synchronization target.

        Returns:
        an invariant UUID created by the Smint.io platform.

        String getContentType()

        Get the name of the binary asset in various languages.
        Returns:
        a single line name of the asset, translated to various languages.

      • getDescription

        Map<Locale,String> getDescription()
        Provide a multi-line description of the binary asset in various languages.
        Returns:
        the multi-line description of the asset, translated to various languages.

      • getUsage

        Map<Locale,String> getUsage()

      • getDownloadUrl

        URL getDownloadUrl()
        Return the download URL to access the content on the Smint.io platform.
        Returns:
        an URL to download the asset.

      • getDownloadedFile

        File getDownloadedFile()
        Downloads the binary from Smint.io platform to a temporary file and provides this file.

        The URL to download from is taken from #getDownloadUrl() and all content stored to a temporary file.

        Returns:
        an already opened InputStream to read bytes from. If the content type is a textual type, the content is encoded with UTF-8.

      • getRecommendedFileName

        String getRecommendedFileName()
        Denotes the recommended file name for the locally stored asset.

        This is an optionally suggestion for the file name. This name is not mandatory, but consumers are strongly advised to use this name.

        Returns:
        a suggestion for a file.

      • getLocale

        Locale getLocale()
        Get the locale this assemble is valid for.

        If this binary asset does not depend on any locale (including language and country) null may be returned.

        Returns:
        a locale this asset is valid for or null if not restricted to any locale.

      • getVersion

        int getVersion()
        Get a version number for this binary asset that can be used for updating the asset.

        Comparing the version number of binary assets enables ISyncTarget to detect updates to the binary data. The higher the version number, the more recent the binary data is.

        Returns:
        a number greater than 0, which is increased by 1 on every update to the binary asset.
